@aaannndddyyy where would you draw the line? Should you also mention the issues with TOR, and with HTTPS in general, or just the toxme implementation? How about when you roll your own toxme? 

My point was, if you're trying to be fancy with 3rd party extensions, that decrease security at the cost of convenience, I don't think that's something we should concern ourselves with. Explaining it to client developers, sure, but the spec isn't for client devs.

(I've also updated my original comment with and additional line to make my original comment more clear.
